    <div class="ians-column">

      <p>During Unit training, OJTIs (and in some phases, STDIs) typically instruct student ATCOs who are starting their first professional job and gaining their first ATC rating. They also instruct more mature ATCOs who may have moved from one sector or unit to another to acquire a new or renew an expired endorsement(s). </p>

      <p>During continuation training, however, the <strong>learners are always the instructor’s peers or colleagues</strong> that s/he works with on a daily bases. As a result, the instructor may need to <strong>modify</strong> their method of instructing. It could include elements of classic instructional techniques with coaching and individual facilitation. Continuation training is an opportunity for the instructor to enable a fellow controller, through guided analysis, to <strong>evaluate for themselves</strong> what is most appropriate and effective.</p>

      <div class="oj-continuation ians-bg-blue-dark">
        <p>
          <strong class="oj-continuation-strong">Continuation training (ATCO.D.075)</strong> aims at maintaining air traffic controllers’ skills and competence, and concerns all <strong>licensed air traffic controllers with a valid unit endorsement</strong> in the Unit. </p>

        {% image "./images/atc-1.jpg", "ATC working"%}
      </div>

      <div class="oj-refresher ians-bg-blue-dark">
        <p class="mt-0">
          <strong>Continuation training:</strong>
        </p>
        <div class="oj-continuation-refresher">
          <p class="mt-0">
            <strong class="oj-continuation-strong">Refresher training (ATCO.D.080)</strong> is a mandatory part of Continuation training that all ATCOs must undertake regularly and has three subjects that must be covered:</p>

          <ul class="list-inside list-disc">
            <li>
              <strong>Standard practices</strong> with communication and phraseology</li>
            <li>
              <strong>Abnormal / emergency</strong> with communication and phraseology</li>
            <li>
              <strong>Human factors</strong>
            </li>
          </ul>

          {% image "./images/atc-2.jpg", "ATC working"%}
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="oj-info-panel-container">

